Response ID: resp_1444
Response Text: There needs to be more emphasis on diverse audiences, not just diverse staff. The grant restructuring favored certain groups without a history of arts programming or track record of actually mentoring and supporting artists. Also, the grant programs were funding organizations outside the ETJ area, sending Austin tax dollars outside of our community. This practice should be stopped immediately. Major cities like Philadelphia, New York, and Chicago do not allow this. Why is Austin? The response we received was that housing costs are high and artists are moving out of Austin. Well, guess what incentivizes them to leave and diminishes our culture? Funding grant programs outside the city. Also, have you been to NYC, Chicago or Philly? Much more expensive places to live. This city needs to mature in its grant-giving. It's not 90s Austin anymore and we need to be better stewards of our limited funds.

